body_text: Let me know if you want me to stop with these, but thought I'd add another sorting algorithm that I find very interesting.
Miscellaneous typos fixed.
Hi, this is fixing the situation when we have an unsorted array with negative numbers and zeroes.

While running property based tests - based on fast-check - on the implementation of knuthMorrisPratt I discovered what seems to be an inconsistency:
knuthMorrisPratt("", "") === -1
knuthMorrisPratt("a", "a") === 0
The tests that discovered the issue are available in the commit: dubzzz@87329dd
If you are interested in this test method, I can issue another pull request for those property based tests.

Created Rabin hash function module.
Transitioned Rabin-Karp string matching function to Rabin hash function family.

Refactored disjoint set data structure
Updated dependencies (Kruskal, Detect Cycles) for new interface.

This implements the fib(n) function that completes in log(n) number of iterations.
Found in SICP https://mitpress.mit.edu/sites/default/files/sicp/full-text/book/book-Z-H-11.html#%_thm_1.19
This adds implementation of Karatsuba multiplication.

Changes:

Add LinkedList traverse implementation
Add LinkedList reverse implementations (reverseTraversal and reverse)
Update their pseudocode
fix typo.

Hi @trekhleb. I just added the ceaserCipher algorithm to your javascript-algorithms repository and it is well tested and documented, I would like you to merge it with the existing repository. Thanks in advance

Translated Queue ("File") and Priority Queue ("File de priorit√©") chapters into french.
Added french language to lang redirection in their respective default readmes.
sam should be sum as a type of range query, which is correctly spelled in the test file.
An algorithm to compute total distinct count of prime factors for a given natural number using the approximate Hardy-Ramanujan algorithm and its comparison with the original accurate algorithm.

Simple change to fix the typo in a comment in RedBlackTree.js
This is to address issue #528
adjusted for better reading of javascript-algorithms.
Added Mini-max sum

Added Horner's Method into algorithms/math. Horner's method is a clever solution named after William George Horner, to evaluate polynomial functions given a certain point. I think it would be an interesting addition since it can be used in many hardware/software applications.

Changes 'a lower' (bound) to 'an upper' (bound)
to reflect presumed meaning.
Just some better Spanish for linked-list README.

Updated original Quicksort README and put a link referencing the Portuguese documentation
Added Turkish readme for Factorial.

Create a factors.js to find the factor of a number which is input by the user.
added a clear check for the factorial eveluation of negative numbers to avoid wrong answer at runtime.

Issue: Factorial of a negative number does not exist #1008
Added condition to throw an error for negative numbers in factorial. Also added test cases to validate the results.

I have corrected the typo in binary search file. here function name should be lessThan() not lessThen()
